{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"962ce28a-3abc-4cc6-ae2c-23652e37ba4e","content":"The `.testsettings` format is **legacy and ignored by modern MSTest**. I migrated your configuration to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what was done:\n\n### Created `local.runsettings`\nEach setting maps as follows:\n\n| `.testsettings` | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `<Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" />` | `<TestSessionTimeout>30000</TestSessionTimeout>` in `<RunConfiguration>` |\n| `<AssemblyResolution>` with `useLoadContext` | `<MSTest><AssemblyResolution>` section |\n| Code coverage `DataCollector` | `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>` section (updated to v2.0 URI) |\n\n### Updated `TestProject.csproj`\nAdded `<RunSettingsFilePath>` so the settings are automatically picked up by `dotnet test` and Visual Studio — no need to pass `--settings` manually.\n\nYou can now **delete `local.testsettings`** once you've verified tests run correctly. If you need a per-test timeout (instead of session-wide), add `[Timeout(30000)]` to individual test methods or use `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout></MSTest>` in the runsettings.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5a2b46a2-2e1e-446b-bc25-c3f2c421b2f3","outputTokens":317,"requestId":"CFCB:B0AF0:6146687:6D52A24:69EC25D0"},"id":"f696ffae-fa20-4c2f-a387-05e8d246a37d","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:24:24.167Z","parentId":"be8741cb-cec7-4cfa-a74e-c153f6d36d3b"}
